This paper is about search behavior in historical news archives and introduces a novel algorithm to support this search strategy. The paper focuses on modeling a historian's search task and defining an aspect-time diversification problem over news archives. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category, which deals with search and retrieval of information from large datasets. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of temporal priors and temporal expressions, which suggests that it may also belong to the Natural Language Processing (cs.CL) and Deep Learning (cs.DL) sub-categories, which deal with processing and understanding natural language and temporal data. The paper also mentions a qualitative user study, which suggests that it may belong to the Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC) sub-category, which deals with the design and evaluation of interactive systems. Finally, the paper deals with historical research, which suggests that it may also belong to the Cybersecurity (cs.CY) sub-category, which deals with the protection of historical data and archives.
